  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A white-box test approach should be taken to verify a unit's internal structure. Theoretically, you should test every&#xD;
    possible path through the code, but that isn't always possible. At the very least you should exercise every&#xD;
    decision-to-decision path (DD-path) at least once because you are then executing all statements at least once. A&#xD;
    decision is typically an if-statement, and a DD-path is a path between two decisions.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To get this level of test coverage, it is recommended that you choose test data so that every decision is evaluated in&#xD;
    every possible way.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
